caption: You guys are the best! Consistently good food and always amazing service. I’ve only gone to a restaurant location once and it was great, but we order delivery often and every single time you guys are so sweet - you wait outside the car to make sure we get our food before driving off and send a friendly wave. Seems small but it’s very appreciated. Thank you!

It's sooo strange! This sushi place has the highest quality sushi in Fenway and Back Bay but people don't know it or something. They always give me double size portions for same and it only costs like 11 bucks for a plate of unagi fried rice or 17 for a double size sake don salmon bowl. Seriously,  most underrated sushi spot in the entire Boston area.

The service was very nice, as was the food.  The maki rolls were flavourful, as well as the edamame and tuna tataki we ordered. The sashimi platter was quite varied, but some of the sashimi was not as flavourful as I would have hoped. Nonetheless, this was overall a good sushi place.
They have this rice with salmon that I used to looove, but can't remember its name since it's been a while since I'v been there.
Tough chewy squid sushi. Should not have eaten it. Upset stomach within an hour. Will not be returning
Very tasty vegetarian options
This place provides good and affordable meals. I like their lunch special

The food here was average and the service was basic. What disturbed me the most about this place was that the sushi chef came in from smoking a cigarette and never washed his hands. After confronting him, he was offended as if I had done something wrong. They are way too comfortable feeding college kids. No care, or mindfulness.

(Translated by Google) Very good restaurant. The waitress a rare kindness, patient because being French and not very used to Japanese food, she took the time to explain and show us the dishes. I recommend .  (Original) Très bon restaurant. La serveuse d'une gentillesse rare, patiente car étant français et pas très habitué à la nourriture japonaise, elle a pris le temps de nous expliqué et de nous montrer les plats. Je recommande .
Just kind of meh...service was good.
Shrimp and steak great but vegetables had no seasonings, sauce or taste- still firm.
Their lunch menu is the best option if you're working near charles station MGH :)

Was told that my celiac could be accommodated, but my sushi roll came with crunchy tempura mixed in with the fillings. Waitress did not know what gluten was, but told us that they were able to make all food gluten free... Had to reiterate many times that we cannot ingest wheat. Service was friendly, but orders were heavily backed up to the point where the waitress apologized and brought us bowls of miso soup for free (which also contained gluten).
Excellent dumplings and chirashi

Too expensive for the amount of food we had. The place is nice and Kenmore is well communicated but there are better places to spend your money. The food is okay but both me and my partner had upset stomachs after.
I always ask for the bento boxes, I find they're the best in the menu for the price given
Food was so-so. Location on Cambridge Street is better

Pretty solid choice for sushi, and pricing isn't too bad for the quality of sushi you get. Can't say for their other offerings, but their menu looks to be quite extensive, and they offer speciality sushis too. Good ambience and service is fast and attentive. Would come back again
Great to get Japanese type food. The service fast, the restaurant is clean, and the atmosphere is serene. Rate 5/7
I took the chicken. Was pretty expensive, bad and dry. However heard that their sushis are good, but I did not try them.
The attitude of my waitress is very bad.
Good food love it, not to many people
Nice food and service is good
Consistently great sushi, have yet to be disappointed

You guys have so many more options to chose from, do not chose this if you wish to have a pleasant night. Read the below... - food: mediocre - service: completely TRASH, the waitress (the Thai lady with long hair) specifically. She showed attitude both in service, as we told her we were short on time and yet, made us wait for the food for over 10 minutes. Also, she showed attitude when she "assumed" we didn't pay for tips, when we specifically told her the amount we calculated already included tips.... so we (a group of 4) ended up arguing and grabbing attention from the other tables. Also, mentioned above, we were in a rush, the argument took over 10 minutes of our time, while "trying" to solve the problem after our clarification, she talked to her fellow worker in another language. This is unacceptable, especially when we said we were in a rush and in general, unacceptable in front of customers. - sorry if this is harsh but I will NEVER step back at this restaurant anytime soon.

Very solid sushi. For apps both the fried dumplings and the spring rolls were good with a slight nod to the spring rolls. We got a wide variety of Maki sushi. Some notable versions were the rainbow roll and the crazy roll. Everything was good. We went back a second night and even though it was quite late they were able to package us up an order to go. A nice place, good ambiance and not terribly expensive. Recommended.
My absolute favorite go-to. Even when they’re crazy busy, my order is always right, always exactly the same quality I expect, and always prompt.
Great sushi 👌
Delicious, well priced sushi in a cozy environment. It is a bit too dark for me but I can excuse that because the sushi is great.
Delicious dishes
One of the best Japanese places I’ve ever eaten at. I’ve been going here for years and years now with my family and it just keeps getting better. I 100% recommend the dumpling soup and all the sushi.
Good service, nice decor and love the lunch specials!

I ordered the eel fried rice, which was tasty except for the fact that there were still some bones in the eel so when I chewed on the rice that is mixed in with the eel, I bit on the bones also. But overall, the taste of the dish was very good and it was just a little under 10 dollars.

Incredibly delicious sushi at amazing prices! The salmon here literally tastes like butter, and when they brought the check, I thought they had missed some things because it was so low. I would recommend the salmon combo (2 maki rolls and a hand roll), the sashimi appetizer (10 pieces of sashimi), and the ocean roll (the honey wasabi sauce is incredible). The service is very quick and attentive, and the place itself is cute and has a nice atmosphere. Would come back again in a heartbeat!

Quality seems pretty good and service was very fast. I got a salmon poke bowl, and my only  complaint is that the mango was quite crunchy. Prices were a bit high, but probably around what you would expect for sushi in Boston. I thought the atmosphere inside was really nice - it's much more spacious than it appears from the outside.
I love this place. The sushi is excellent and it has a cool atmosphere.
My brother works there and it's great
Good shrimp tempura. Fast service. Not crowded
Recommended for lunch M-F. The bento boxes are delicious and inexpensive.
Great food! Friendly staff!
Got horrible food poisoning within 2 hours of eating there.
Decent prices!!! Excellent food and good customer service! My favorites place to eat sushi!

Good solid sushi place with several other locations in Boston. They don't try to be anything they arent with good sushi and a relaxed atmosphere. Typically quiet compared to other places in and around Fenway/Kenmore during sox games. Prices are average for the area.
I love them. Good quality accompanied with a large portion, makes this place worth the money spend.
Food was good, a little pricey.   Service was mediocre at best.
Fantastic food.
Good food but terrible service. Rude staff! Never going back there!
Reasonable price. Great quality
Great food and fast service, reasonable price. All we ordered was more than expected. The pokè bowl was to die for!🇦🇪

The WORST restaurant EVER!  So RUDE, so RUDE, so RUDE, so UNPROFESSIONAL.  They are completely DISHONEST.  The website says they are open until 11:15, we call and verify, they assure us that we can order take-out until 10:30, we call at 10:15 and they do not pick up the phone, then we physically went to the restaurant and the staff was gone and the restaurant was closed.  The manager denied knowing anything about this, even though we VERIFIED with him that the restaurant was open, he was rude and even more unprofessional than his staff.  Also, the food is completely mediocre, the noodles are soggy, the fish is dry, the sushi is mostly rice, and the tempura is very greasy!  Try Kaju instead - a wonderful restaurant, with professional and courteous staff.
Food is fantastic, decor is average at best but the food and service is amazing
Great sushi and very fresh fish. Love the decor too.
Good value lunch deals! Good tastes, solid portions, excellent value.
Food is not good. Dried out chicken teriyaki.  Sushi rice in chirashi too much vinegar.
Yummy sushi. 🍣
Sushi is always fresh and the flavors are great. Good price for what you get.
Trendy sushi bar aimed at the yuppie crowd. Loud dance music makes it less than ideal for families. Reasonably priced and a good spot for lunch with its bento box specials.

Got the chicken teriyaki, very disappointing. Only one small breast and for $8-9, that's way too little. Sauce was off, tasted funny. Salad was too fancy. The roll (not sure what it was) was good. I expect much more and better tasting for the price range. Would not recommend
fire sushi
Surprisingly fast service, quality sashimi, and cant beat the location with a stick. Would recommend ordering ahead for take out.
Beef Noodle Soup.

All around bad service and food.  Staff couldn't be bothered to do a good job, and was vaguely rude.  Menu was outright deceptive; the bento boxes say that they come with soup, salad, rice, and fruit, but upon ordering one of these I was told it also came with fried spring rolls and (another item I can't remember), so I cancelled the order and got something else. However,  two others at my table ordered bento boxes, and they only came with soup (none of the other listed things actually came with it), and weren't even contained in a proper bento box.  In addition, the food was gross; the plates seemed to have random smudges of food all over them, and the fish made me slightly ill.  TL;DR: Menu is made of lies, everything else is of marginal quality.  Additional warning to people with allergies: do not come here.  Normally, as someone with allergies to dairy, nuts, and eggs, I've found that sushi places are the best at accommodating my allergies; the process of making sushi involves careful use and cleaning of ingredients, work space, and utensils. Here, this was not the case. Our waitress seemed annoyed when I asked about the ingredients in something I was planning on ordering, and I even got the idea that she didn't intend on doing it at all, so I politely reminded her a few times. Even then, once we received the food, the plates seemed to have random smudges of food all over them, and I had to send one item back because I found tempura flakes on it (tempura flakes had nothing to do with this dish, and are not safe for me to eat). I would not trust them again by any means.  TL;DR PT. 2: Don't trust with allergies.
Good sushi near BU and Fenway park. Good lunch specials, too

We walked in about 1:45 and few customers were about, i think only one table with customers ready to leave. The proprietor directed us to one of the oddly designed tiny wall mounted tables, and strangely to one way in the back (in a completely empty room). I asked him if we could sit at one of the nice front window tables. That was the waiting area. My mistake. Then, simply asked if we could sit at a table near the front, but were told we could not; otherwise, we must wait in the waiting area until the table was set. The only table that was NOT set was another tiny two person square (2' x 2'). We were not "allowed" to sit at a larger table (per customer request) in what was otherwise a completely empty restaurant. Simply put, the man at reception was a being real a**hole. We left.

Nice place for a relaxing dinner.  Kind of a weird setup but I can see how it works for couples or groups.  Food is tasty. Been here many times and your standard sushi selections if you looking for the familiar. Nothing remarkable but that's a good thing in this area where it's either packed or out of business, and this place has lasting appeal.  Good place for dates as you can actually hear each other. The pricing is reasonable as well.
Great bento box lunch specials and the sushi is very good
Owned by the same people who own Symphony Sushi. The entire menu is identical if I recall. Good food though.
Very nise! Good sushi!
The service was good, but they messed up my take out order. I only ordered two things so it wouldn't have been that hard. Make sure you check your order before you leave.

The food is of high quality and is very fairly priced. The excellent decor combines Japan's traditional minimalist elegance with a modernist feel. Their tables for two are triangles with the long edge against the wall, allowing couples to sit adjacent  and enjoy a more intimate dining experience. Good place for a casual but elegant date.
The staff was incredibly helpful, I accidentally ordered to the wrong Fins so they just re-made my order there and canceled the one at the other location without me even having to ask!
Good, cheap, average sushi
Fin's is mediocre. Not too expensive, but not too high quality. Get it if it's convenient, but don't go out of your way to try it.

I really love their lunch bento box.  Saves me the terrible choice of what to get!  Their takeout is also fast and fresh.  Its a pretty good price, and you can tell its fresh so its pretty worth it.  The restaurant is classy and quiet, good for small groups or pairs, but probably wouldn't go with a large group.  Also I think their miso soup is one of my favorites in the city, which is funny because they're all kind of exactly the same.
Great experience for the lunch. Very nice and fare price.

Fin's Sushi is probably my favorite sushi place in Boston. Decent price, excellent food, and quick delivery if you choose to order out. I have honestly never had a bad experience here. The menu gives a large selection of rolls, some a bit more expensive than others, but in the end they are all top notch. Love the atmosphere of the place as well.
Excellent sushi for the price. This is one of my favorite places to visit with friends or dine in. I recommend the Yellow Fin roll or the Double Match Maki.
Amazing! Best fried rice in pc/PCB area.
Great value at lunch food is good ambience is good
great atmosphere and located right in the heart of kenmore square; best sushi in the area at an affordable price.  great for dine in or for take out!  don't miss out on the lunch specials, either!
Good sushi! Try the Mexican rolls.
Quite nice rolls. My best friend is a sucker for the Mexican Roll (a must try if you go).  And they have Mochi ice cream!  Overall good value and nice sushi
